    <subfield code="y">00001 Plots of the embedding function $z(r)$ for various values of the $\beta$-parameter are shown. The throat width has been set to $r_0=1$. The embedding of each slice $t=const, \theta=\frac{\pi}{2}$, $\beta=const$ of the wormhole~(\ref{metric LM MT}) extends from the throat $r_0=1$ to $r_{max}>r_0$. The heigh of the $z$-function increases with decreasing $\beta$-parameter. It becomes clear that as $\beta \rightarrow -\infty$ the $r_{max} \rightarrow r_0=1$.</subfield>
